b'RT @afspnational: Q4: We\xe2\x80\x99re trying to reduce the suicide rate 20 percent by 2025. What can you do to #StopSuicide?'
b'@MrsCherylVinson @NavStress @afspnational Thank you for sharing this. \xf0\x9f\x92\x9a'
b'A3. To be able to care for the people you love, you must first take care of yourself. https://t.co/AjX3rYOooK #StopSuicide'
b'A3. Remember, taking care of yourself is a valid goal on its own, and it helps you support the people you love. #StopSuicide'
b'A3. If the steps you\xe2\x80\x99ve taken aren\xe2\x80\x99t working, it may be time to share with a mental health professional https://t.co/zkkE2bVSPh #StopSuicide'
b'- Talk to someone. Get support from friends, family, a counselor or a support group. Talking can help.'
b'- Get creative. Some people use art as their release. Try out a class for writing, painting, dance, music or improv!'
b'- Set aside time for yourself. Do something that makes you feel good, like reading, going to the movies or getting a massage.'
b'- Manage your time. Make a schedule so you don\xe2\x80\x99t feel overwhelmed by everyday tasks and deadlines.'
b'A3. Try different coping strategies to find the best one that fits for your #mentalhealth. Here\xe2\x80\x99s a thread with some ideas\xe2\x80\xa6 \n\n#StopSuicide'
b'- Practice relaxation exercises. Deep breathing, meditation and progressive muscle relaxation are easy, quick ways to reduce stress.'
b'- Avoid alcohol and drugs. They don\xe2\x80\x99t actually reduce stress and often worsen it.'
b'- Get enough sleep. Adults generally need between 7-9 hours of sleep. Avoid using computers, TV and smartphones before bed.'
b'- Eat well. Eating foods like whole grains, vegetables & fresh fruit is key to a healthy body & helps stabilize your energy levels and mood.'
b'- Exercise daily. Take the stairs whenever possible, walk up escalators, and run and bike rather than drive.'
b'A3. Improving your physical wellbeing is one of the best ways you can support your #mentalhealth. Here\xe2\x80\x99s a thread with tips\xe2\x80\xa6 #StopSuicide'
b'A3. Everyone experiences stress. Finding effective ways to manage stress is important. https://t.co/Qi4RINNnv9 \n\n#StopSuicide'
b'A3. Once you know which situations cause you stress, you\xe2\x80\x99ll be prepared to avoid it and to cope with it when it happens. #StopSuicide'
b'A3. Begin by identifying how stress feels to you. Then identify what events or situations cause you to feel that way. #StopSuicide'
b'- Aches, pains, and tense muscles\n- Insomnia'
b'- Upset stomach, including diarrhea, constipation and nausea'
b'- Headaches\n- Low energy'

b'- Get help from organizations specializing in crisis intervention and suicide prevention, like @800273TALK, @CrisisTextLine & @afspnational'
b'- Don\xe2\x80\x99t be sworn to secrecy. Seek support if you feel that you are not adequately able to provide the help they need and deserve.'
b'- If necessary, take action by removing means such as weapons or stockpiled pills.'
b'- Get involved and become available. Show interest and support them through what they are going through.'
b'- Be supportive. Minimizing their problems or giving advice may create distance between you.'
b'- Be non-judgmental. Don\xe2\x80\x99t debate with them whether suicide is right or wrong or whether their feelings are good or bad.'
b'- Be willing to listen and allow them to express their feelings. Accept that their feelings are valid.'
b'- Be direct. Talk openly and honestly about suicide. Don\xe2\x80\x99t be afraid to ask directly if they are thinking about suicide.'
